senses.sense_definition: Situated or occurring between the kidneys.

examples.text: The biologist carefully examined the <w>interrenal</w> tissue under a high-powered microscope.
Hormone secretion in this species is primarily managed by <w>interrenal</w> cells.

senses.sense_definition: The interrenal gland, an organ found in many fishes.

examples.text: Scientists studied the <w>interrenal</w> to understand how the fish responds to environmental stress.
The anatomy of the <w>interrenal</w> in sharks differs slightly from that of bony fish.
